WEBVTT

00:13.999 --> 00:15.999
- Previously
on "Below Deck"...

00:15.999 --> 00:17.999
They want to do a white party.
- White party. That's easy.

00:17.999 --> 00:18.999
- Try and schedule a shark dive
with 'em.

00:19.000 --> 00:20.999
That's on their bucket list.

00:21.000 --> 00:22.999
- Hey, girl.
Hey, don't get excited.

00:22.999 --> 00:25.999
- Oh, my gosh! Is that a picture
of Ryan Gosling?

00:25.999 --> 00:27.999
- They're dressed so fun.
- Welcome aboard.

00:27.999 --> 00:28.999
- He is hot.

00:28.999 --> 00:30.999
- Did you see his style
with his, like, loafers?

00:30.999 --> 00:32.999
Oh, my goodness.

00:32.999 --> 00:33.999
- Don't throw that box away.

00:33.999 --> 00:34.999
Just leave the box
where it is. Thank you.

00:34.999 --> 00:35.999
- You're being
a little bit jerky.

00:35.999 --> 00:37.999
- You dish it,
you'll get it back.

00:37.999 --> 00:40.999
- Are you getting burned out?
- Me? No.

00:40.999 --> 00:42.999
- You get these certain dishes
you like with the charters,

00:42.999 --> 00:44.999
so you just keep doing them?
- Yeah.

00:44.999 --> 00:46.999
- Okay, I get it, Kate.

00:46.999 --> 00:48.999
- Oh, Smokey Robinson.

00:53.999 --> 00:55.999
- Eduardo says "yes."
[giggles]

00:55.999 --> 00:59.999
I know this is wrong,
but, hey, she's got a nice ass.

00:59.999 --> 01:02.999
- What the [bleep]?
Does that look clean?

01:02.999 --> 01:04.999
Does that look clean?
- No way.

01:04.999 --> 01:06.999
- That's a flame!
That's a flame.

01:06.999 --> 01:08.999
- That's a fire.
- That's a fire!

01:08.999 --> 01:09.999
- What is going on?
[smoke alarm beeping]

01:09.999 --> 01:13.999
- Eddie, Kate--
- Where's the fire extinguisher?

01:13.999 --> 01:15.999
- [snores]

01:15.999 --> 01:16.999
[air horn blows]

01:16.999 --> 01:19.999
[upbeat music]

01:19.999 --> 01:27.999
♪ ♪

01:31.999 --> 01:32.999
- It's a fire.
That's a fire.

01:32.999 --> 01:35.999
- Eddie, we need you
in the galley, please.

01:35.999 --> 01:36.999
There's an actual fire
in the oven.

01:36.999 --> 01:39.999
[smoke alarm beeping]

01:39.999 --> 01:41.999
- It smells like fire.

01:41.999 --> 01:43.999
- What's that fire alarm for?

01:45.999 --> 01:47.999
- Close the door!

01:47.999 --> 01:48.999
Close the door!

01:48.999 --> 01:49.999
- Here.

01:49.999 --> 01:52.999
[dramatic music]

01:52.999 --> 01:57.999
♪ ♪

01:57.999 --> 02:00.999
- [exhales sharply]
I can't do that.

02:03.999 --> 02:04.999
- Never in my life.

02:04.999 --> 02:06.999
- Eddie. Eddie.
Lee.

02:06.999 --> 02:08.999
[walkie-talkie clatters]

02:08.999 --> 02:10.999
- Go ahead, Lee.

02:10.999 --> 02:12.999
- What's going on down there?

02:12.999 --> 02:14.000
- There was a fire
in the oven.

02:14.000 --> 02:15.999
- Do we have it contained?
- Yes.

02:16.000 --> 02:17.999
- Copy.
The fire's been contained.

02:17.999 --> 02:19.999
I'm standing by still
with a fire extinguisher.

02:19.999 --> 02:20.999
- I'm on my way.

02:21.000 --> 02:23.999
- Really?
A [bleep] fire?

02:23.999 --> 02:24.999
Obviously,
a [bleep] pizza caught fire.

02:24.999 --> 02:26.999
Back up from...

02:26.999 --> 02:28.999
- There was a pan
with a pizza on it,

02:28.999 --> 02:30.999
and then there was two pans
in there.

02:30.999 --> 02:32.999
Usually you
take the other pans out,

02:32.999 --> 02:35.999
and the other pans
were just sitting on there.

02:35.999 --> 02:37.999
- The pans were on the grill.

02:37.999 --> 02:38.999
- This is Kate's fault.

02:38.999 --> 02:41.999
Why would you throw a pizza
in the oven with other [bleep]

02:41.999 --> 02:43.999
in the oven?

02:43.999 --> 02:44.999
Who does that?

02:44.999 --> 02:47.999
And then I went to go
pull this open,

02:47.999 --> 02:49.000
and that was, like, whoa.

02:49.000 --> 02:51.999
- A captain would rather hear
anything else than "fire."

02:51.999 --> 02:53.999
A boat this size

02:53.999 --> 02:56.999
can burn down to the waterline
in five minutes.

02:56.999 --> 02:58.999
- I keep hearing
this alarm go off,

02:58.999 --> 03:00.999
and then I'm like,
"Wait. I smell something.

03:00.999 --> 03:02.999
This is not right."

03:02.999 --> 03:03.999
- So it's my fault?

03:03.999 --> 03:05.999
- I'm so sorry.

03:05.999 --> 03:06.999
- We almost had a fire.

03:06.999 --> 03:07.999
I mean, was there actual fire?

03:07.999 --> 03:09.999
- Yeah.
There was an actual fire.

03:09.999 --> 03:11.999
- No, there's no fire.
- But it's out now.

03:11.999 --> 03:14.999
I have never had a fire
on any yacht

03:14.999 --> 03:16.999
I've ever worked on.

03:18.999 --> 03:21.000
- I just tried to, like, get
a quick shot and extinguish it

03:21.999 --> 03:24.000
and then close the door
and just not let it flare up.

03:26.999 --> 03:29.999
- Rocky and Kate.
- No. I don't think so.

03:29.999 --> 03:32.999
I went up to do the DVD player
and left Rocky here.

03:32.999 --> 03:34.999
- I don't know if it was
because of the sheet trays

03:34.999 --> 03:35.999
are in there or...

03:35.999 --> 03:38.000
- Rocky keeps going on and on
about how I should have taken

03:38.999 --> 03:39.999
the trays out,
but guess what.

03:39.999 --> 03:41.999
If the oven is anything
like the rest of the galley,

03:41.999 --> 03:44.999
it's definitely covered
in grease.

03:46.999 --> 03:49.999
I'm sorry
for the rude awakening.

03:54.999 --> 03:55.999
Okay.

03:59.999 --> 04:01.999
I'm not taking the blame
for this one.

04:01.999 --> 04:03.999
Leon should take the blame.

04:11.999 --> 04:13.999
- Hey, Amy.

04:13.999 --> 04:14.999
- Hey.

04:14.999 --> 04:16.999
- How you doing?
- Whew.

04:16.999 --> 04:18.999
Doing okay.
How are you doing?

04:18.999 --> 04:19.999
- Tired.
- I bet you are.

04:19.999 --> 04:20.999
You were up late, huh?

04:20.999 --> 04:22.999
- Yeah. 3:00.
- Oh, my goodness.

04:22.999 --> 04:23.999
- Today's gonna be a great day.

04:24.000 --> 04:25.999
Everyone's really exhausted,

04:25.999 --> 04:28.999
and now we have a fire
to blame on someone.

04:28.999 --> 04:30.999
God, I'm tired.

04:34.999 --> 04:35.999
- I'm going to take
the primary coffees.

04:36.000 --> 04:39.999
We're going to do breakfast
up top at the bridge table.

04:40.999 --> 04:42.999
He didn't hear the fire alarm.

04:42.999 --> 04:43.999
This note's definitely
not fazing him.

04:43.999 --> 04:45.999
So, if he doesn't think
it was a big deal

04:45.999 --> 04:46.999
there was a fire in his galley,

04:46.999 --> 04:49.999
I'm not going to say anything
to him.

04:49.999 --> 04:50.999
- I don't know
how you slept through that.

04:50.999 --> 04:52.999
It was so loud.

04:52.999 --> 04:54.999
- There's gonna be
a lot of drama.

04:54.999 --> 04:57.999
[pop rock music]

04:57.999 --> 05:00.999
♪ ♪

05:01.000 --> 05:04.000
- Our charter guest is
celebrating his 50th birthday.

05:04.000 --> 05:06.999
It gives us a chance
to distract them,

05:06.999 --> 05:07.999
forget about last night.

05:07.999 --> 05:09.999
The guests
have a late departure,

05:09.999 --> 05:11.999
so we just need
to get through today.

05:14.999 --> 05:16.999
- So did they tell you
what happened with the oven?

05:17.000 --> 05:18.999
- Well, I don't know.

05:18.999 --> 05:20.999
I don't know whether
we spilled some juices--

05:20.999 --> 05:21.999
- Okay, so I'll tell you
what's up.

05:21.999 --> 05:23.999
I'll tell you
what [bleep] happened.

05:23.999 --> 05:24.999
Kate was making pizza
in the oven.

05:24.999 --> 05:26.999
So I open it.

05:26.999 --> 05:29.999
A ton of smoke comes out,
and I was like, "Oh, my God."

05:29.999 --> 05:31.999
Two extra pans in there.

05:31.999 --> 05:32.999
You know how you,
like, keep them?

05:32.999 --> 05:34.999
But usually if you're using
the oven to cook...

05:34.999 --> 05:36.999
- You take it out.
- You take out the other pans.

05:36.999 --> 05:37.999
- I don't know what happened,

05:37.999 --> 05:39.999
but, I mean, by that time,
I was out cold.

05:39.999 --> 05:40.999
I was asleep.

05:40.999 --> 05:42.999
So I do believe
Kate is just waiting

05:42.999 --> 05:45.999
for me to fall flat on my face.

05:45.999 --> 05:48.999
- Actually really scary.
It was really scary.

05:52.999 --> 05:54.999
- Cross your fingers
nothing spills, Leon.

05:54.999 --> 05:56.999
- Okay, fingers crossed.

05:56.999 --> 05:59.999
- Okay.
For the birthday boy.

05:59.999 --> 06:02.999
[knock at door]

06:02.999 --> 06:04.999
With breakfast in bed,
on the stewardess side,

06:04.999 --> 06:05.999
it can be
a little bit awkward,

06:06.000 --> 06:08.999
because you can potentially walk
in on someone naked.

06:08.999 --> 06:11.999
Is it okay
if I come bring it to y'all?

06:11.999 --> 06:13.999
Happy birthday.
- Oh, thank you.

06:13.999 --> 06:15.999
[laughs]
- Whoo!

06:15.999 --> 06:18.999
So I got some black coffee,
some Baileys on the side.

06:18.999 --> 06:20.999
- Perfect.
- Great. Okay, enjoy.

06:20.999 --> 06:21.999
Happy birthday, Alan.
- Thank you.

06:21.999 --> 06:23.999
- You're welcome.

06:23.999 --> 06:25.999
Thank you, Jesus.

06:25.999 --> 06:28.999
[lively dance music]

06:28.999 --> 06:30.999
♪ ♪

06:30.999 --> 06:34.999
[cell phone rings]
- Hello?

06:34.999 --> 06:35.999
- Hello, Captain Lee?

06:35.999 --> 06:37.999
This is Keith over
at Dive Abaco.

06:37.999 --> 06:38.999
- Hey, Keith.
How you doing today?

06:38.999 --> 06:39.999
- I'm all right.

06:39.999 --> 06:42.999
Plan to be ready to take off
at about 10:30.

06:42.999 --> 06:43.999
- Yeah. That works.

06:43.999 --> 06:45.999
I can send 'em over
in our little boat.

06:45.999 --> 06:47.999
- Yeah, that'll work.
Okay.

06:47.999 --> 06:49.999
- At least
something's going right today.

06:49.999 --> 06:51.999
The guests finally get
to do their shark diving,

06:51.999 --> 06:53.999
so we get to scratch that
off their bucket list.

06:53.999 --> 06:56.999
Connie, Connie. Lee.
[walkie-talkie beeps]

06:56.999 --> 06:57.999
- Yes, Lee?

06:57.999 --> 06:58.999
- Come up
to the wheelhouse, please.

06:58.999 --> 06:59.999
- On my way.

07:02.999 --> 07:04.999
Hi.

07:04.999 --> 07:06.999
- You're comfy
pulling the anchor up?

07:06.999 --> 07:08.999
- Yes.
- Okay.

07:08.999 --> 07:09.999
Is Emile up?
- Yes.

07:09.999 --> 07:11.999
- Take him up there with you.
- Okay.

07:11.999 --> 07:12.999
Eddie had a really late night,

07:12.999 --> 07:14.999
so he's not going to be
on the bow with me

07:14.999 --> 07:15.999
to lift the anchor.

07:15.999 --> 07:18.999
So it's my turn to do it
by myself.

07:18.999 --> 07:20.999
- Emile, will you come
to the bow with me?

07:20.999 --> 07:22.999
- Yeah. And lift up anchor?
- Yeah.

07:22.999 --> 07:25.999
Here it's 200 feet
of chain out.

07:25.999 --> 07:26.999
It could be wrapped
around boulders.

07:26.999 --> 07:28.999
It could be just laid out
on sand. It could be zigzag.

07:28.999 --> 07:31.999
It could be changing direction
at any point.

07:31.999 --> 07:33.999
Is the chain tight?
Is it slack?

07:33.999 --> 07:35.999
Is it at 12:00?
Is it under the bow?

07:35.999 --> 07:37.999
Does he need a thrust?

07:37.999 --> 07:38.999
Like, he has no idea.
He can't see it.

07:38.999 --> 07:40.999
It is nerve-racking.

07:45.000 --> 07:47.999
- Is Connie doing this anchor
by herself?

07:47.999 --> 07:49.999
- She can handle it.

07:49.999 --> 07:50.999
- Yeah, she can.

07:50.999 --> 07:52.000
I know she's ready for it.

07:52.999 --> 07:53.999
I'm so proud, Connie.

07:53.999 --> 07:55.999
This is, like,
a father's moment.

07:57.999 --> 07:59.999
I think she's nervous.

07:59.999 --> 08:00.999
- She'll be fine.

08:04.000 --> 08:07.999
[clanking]

08:07.999 --> 08:08.999
Bam.

08:08.999 --> 08:11.000
That bitch is home.

08:11.999 --> 08:13.999
Whoo-hoo.
- Nice job.

08:13.999 --> 08:15.999
- I taught her well.

08:18.999 --> 08:20.999
What time did Kate
get to sleep last night?

08:20.999 --> 08:22.999
- About 4:00.
- Jeez.

08:22.999 --> 08:25.999
Did you get some sleep?
- No, I was too wired up.

08:25.999 --> 08:27.999
Did you see the pizza come out?

08:27.999 --> 08:29.999
- The flames were on the bottom
of the oven...

08:29.999 --> 08:32.999
underneath the pizza.

08:32.999 --> 08:34.999
- And Rocky was the one
that discovered it?

08:34.999 --> 08:36.000
- Yep.

08:36.999 --> 08:37.999
- I just want to get
through today...

08:37.999 --> 08:39.999
- Yes, sir.
- And get this thing to the dock

08:39.999 --> 08:43.999
and make our guests
happy, happy, happy.

08:43.999 --> 08:45.999
- I worked for 21 hours.
It was awesome.

08:45.999 --> 08:46.999
- Holy crap.

08:46.999 --> 08:48.000
Like, I heard the alarm,

08:48.999 --> 08:49.999
but I kind of thought
it was, like, a dream.

08:49.999 --> 08:50.999
Then I heard "fire."

08:51.000 --> 08:52.999
I thought
it was 'cause of the pizza.

08:52.999 --> 08:54.999
- The pizza
was still frozen.

08:54.999 --> 08:57.000
The fire only happened because
Leon should have maybe...

08:57.999 --> 08:58.999
both: Cleaned the oven.
- Yeah.

08:58.999 --> 08:59.999
[cork pops]

08:59.999 --> 09:02.999
- Happy birthday!
[all cheering]

09:02.999 --> 09:04.999
- Whoo!
- Happy birthday.

09:04.999 --> 09:06.999
- Yoo-hoo!

09:06.999 --> 09:08.999
- I'm just glad it doesn't smell
like burnt popcorn today.

09:08.999 --> 09:11.999
- I'm just glad the boat
didn't burn down last night.

09:11.999 --> 09:12.999
[laughter]

09:12.999 --> 09:15.999
- Happy birthday.
- Cheers.

09:15.999 --> 09:17.999
- Cheers.
- We love you.

09:17.999 --> 09:18.999
- On my mark,
give me 200 feet.

09:18.999 --> 09:19.999
On my mark.

09:19.999 --> 09:22.999
- Copy. 200.

09:22.999 --> 09:25.999
- Okay.
- And let's drop.

09:25.999 --> 09:28.999
[clanking]

09:28.999 --> 09:29.999
- 200 is out.

09:29.999 --> 09:31.999
- We're going to make
your birthday a memorable one.

09:31.999 --> 09:34.999
- Oh, jeez, it's already
been pretty memorable.

09:34.999 --> 09:36.999
- Oh, no.
Today's the coup de grace.

09:36.999 --> 09:38.999
What do you say
we do that shark dive today?

09:38.999 --> 09:41.999
- Can't wait.
It's a good birthday to have.

09:41.999 --> 09:42.999
- Oh, yeah.

09:42.999 --> 09:44.999
- Attention, deck crew.

09:44.999 --> 09:46.999
The guests are making their way
down to the tender.

09:51.999 --> 09:52.999
- We'll see you
in a little bit.

09:52.999 --> 09:54.999
- Fire 'em up.
Let's get 'em out of here.

09:54.999 --> 09:58.999
- Aw, I'm staying.
Jenny and I will just drink.

09:58.999 --> 09:59.999
- Okay.

09:59.999 --> 10:01.999
- [laughs]

10:02.999 --> 10:03.999
- Hey, deck crew, deck crew.

10:03.999 --> 10:06.999
Danielle and Jenny
were thinking they would like

10:06.999 --> 10:10.999
to be taken to the beach
just off our starboard aft.

10:10.999 --> 10:11.999
- See you guys in a little.

10:11.999 --> 10:14.999
- Con, I'm making to-go
bloody Mary stuff for them.

10:14.999 --> 10:16.999
They both have a full one,
but I'm going to make, like,

10:16.999 --> 10:19.999
two water bottles for them.

10:19.999 --> 10:20.999
She heard me?

10:20.999 --> 10:22.999
- I'm just going to go
kind of around here

10:23.000 --> 10:24.999
if it's calm around the corner.

10:24.999 --> 10:25.999
- Yeah, I mean, go down there,
go around the corner there.

10:25.999 --> 10:27.999
Careful going
through that cut,

10:27.999 --> 10:29.999
'cause, you know,
it's really shallow, obviously.

10:29.999 --> 10:30.999
- Peace out.

10:30.999 --> 10:32.999
[laughs]
- Peace out, Cub Scout.

10:32.999 --> 10:34.999
- Y'all have fun.
Enjoy your exploration.

10:34.999 --> 10:38.999
Okay.
Everyone is gone.

10:38.999 --> 10:41.999
Birthday-morning success.

10:41.999 --> 10:44.999
- Kate, Kate. Lee.

10:44.999 --> 10:46.999
Yeah, do you have a second
to come up to bridge?

10:46.999 --> 10:48.999
- Sure, I just got on deck.

10:48.999 --> 10:51.999
This fire has me
so overwhelmed.

10:51.999 --> 10:52.999
I'm freaking out.

10:52.999 --> 10:55.999
[dramatic music]

10:55.999 --> 10:57.999
♪ ♪

10:57.999 --> 10:58.999
- Coming up....

10:58.999 --> 11:00.999
- I can't have it
going like it is.

11:00.999 --> 11:01.999
- Well, what do you want
to do about it?

11:01.999 --> 11:02.999
You need to make that call.

11:02.999 --> 11:04.999
- I'm done.

11:04.999 --> 11:07.999
- Have a little more respect
for your job and for your--

11:07.999 --> 11:08.999
- Rocky's in the water.
[water splashes]

11:14.999 --> 11:16.999
of just what you observed.

11:16.999 --> 11:18.999
I'm going to have to interview
everybody one at a time,

11:18.999 --> 11:20.999
'cause if I get everybody
in a room,

11:20.999 --> 11:21.999
it's just going to turn

11:21.999 --> 11:23.999
into a he-said-she-said
cluster[bleep].

11:23.999 --> 11:28.999
- So the guests were hungry,
and it was about 1:55.

11:28.999 --> 11:30.999
I found a frozen pizza
in the freezer.

11:30.999 --> 11:32.999
I put the pizza in,
and Rocky came down,

11:32.999 --> 11:34.999
and she said the guests want
to watch movies

11:34.999 --> 11:35.999
and have popcorn.

11:35.999 --> 11:38.999
- Kate was making popcorn,
and Kate was making pizza.

11:38.999 --> 11:39.999
- And she goes,
"But I don't know how

11:39.999 --> 11:42.999
to work the movie player
in the Sky Lounge."

11:42.999 --> 11:44.999
I was like, "Okay, well,
I'll go handle that."

11:44.999 --> 11:46.999
And the popcorn
was beginning to pop.

11:46.999 --> 11:47.999
- Oh, Jesus.

11:47.999 --> 11:49.999
Kate put the freaking popcorn
in too long.

11:49.999 --> 11:53.999
Then I realize it's smoking,
so I go check the microwave,

11:53.999 --> 11:55.999
and the popcorn is burnt,

11:55.999 --> 11:56.999
and then I was like,
"I think she said

11:56.999 --> 11:58.999
she was making a pizza."

11:58.999 --> 12:00.999
So I open the oven, and a whole
bunch of smoke comes out,

12:00.999 --> 12:02.999
and then I see
that there's a flame.

12:02.999 --> 12:04.999
That's a flame.
- Holy hell! Open the door!

12:04.999 --> 12:06.999
- I heard her say,
"Oh, that's a fire."

12:06.999 --> 12:07.999
She opened up the oven door,
and I looked in,

12:07.999 --> 12:09.999
and there was a fire.
- Okay.

12:09.999 --> 12:11.999
- There were lots of flames
in the back of the oven.

12:11.999 --> 12:12.999
- So that's what happened.

12:12.999 --> 12:14.999
- Okay.

12:14.999 --> 12:15.999
Was there anything
on the pans?

12:15.999 --> 12:18.000
No meat or anything
in the pans?

12:18.999 --> 12:20.999
- Usually when you
cook in an oven,

12:20.999 --> 12:22.999
if there's anything else,
you pull it out

12:22.999 --> 12:23.999
before you start cooking.

12:23.999 --> 12:26.999
Um....
- Anything else?

12:26.999 --> 12:28.999
- She's been treating Leon
