- It's disrespectful.

37:08.999 --> 37:10.999
- Where's the [bleep]
communication there?

37:10.999 --> 37:12.999
I don't know.

37:12.999 --> 37:14.999
- You need
to calm down, honey.

37:17.999 --> 37:19.999
- Let's eat.

37:22.999 --> 37:24.999
- I hope this goes over
better than the oysters did.

37:26.999 --> 37:27.999
- That's a good steak.

37:27.999 --> 37:29.999
Their cooking here is amazing.
- Perfect.

37:29.999 --> 37:31.999
- I don't think
I've ever had a bad meal here.

37:31.999 --> 37:33.999
- Thank you, Jesus.

37:33.999 --> 37:35.999
We just dodged an Oreo bullet.

37:35.999 --> 37:37.999
- Would anybody like
a glass of...?

37:37.999 --> 37:38.999
- Yes.

37:40.999 --> 37:43.999
- Well, actually,
he's fallen ill.

37:43.999 --> 37:44.999
- Oh. That's a bummer.

37:44.999 --> 37:45.999
- Yes. Unfortunately,

37:45.999 --> 37:48.999
Leon has fallen ill
with unemployment-itis,

37:48.999 --> 37:50.999
and there's no way
I'm bringing Rocky up here.

37:54.999 --> 37:57.999
- Hey, Kate, could you meet me
on the main deck aft, please?

37:57.999 --> 37:58.999
Ah!

37:58.999 --> 37:59.999
- Copy.

38:01.999 --> 38:03.999
- Delivery.
- Thanks.

38:03.999 --> 38:04.999
- World's heaviest cake...
- [laughs]

38:05.000 --> 38:06.999
- And I don't know what that is,
and I don't know where--

38:06.999 --> 38:09.999
- Oh. These are lava cupcakes.

38:09.999 --> 38:11.999
Holy...
- Oh.

38:11.999 --> 38:12.999
Hmm.

38:12.999 --> 38:14.999
And it's a disaster.

38:14.999 --> 38:16.999
And our sweet charter guest

38:16.999 --> 38:18.999
has never had a birthday cake
in his life.

38:18.999 --> 38:20.999
At this point,
I'm just, like, delirious.

38:20.999 --> 38:22.999
I cannot have
another thing go wrong.

38:22.999 --> 38:24.999
Look at the cake, Amy.
- Hmm.

38:24.999 --> 38:26.999
- Can we fix it with a spoon
and some whipped cream?

38:26.999 --> 38:27.999
- Mm-hmm, mm-hmm, mm-hmm.
- Okay.

38:27.999 --> 38:30.999
Maybe some love,
some shaved chocolate.

38:30.999 --> 38:31.999
- These guys are just so cool.

38:31.999 --> 38:33.999
They're people
you want to hang out with.

38:33.999 --> 38:35.999
- Everything's going
smoothly upstairs.

38:35.999 --> 38:37.999
Now, downstairs--
much different story.

38:37.999 --> 38:39.999
I just kind of fixed it
with my finger.

38:39.999 --> 38:40.999
- Do you want candles?

38:40.999 --> 38:41.999
- But I don't think
they'll notice.

38:41.999 --> 38:43.000
Yeah, we've got candles.

38:43.000 --> 38:46.999
Hopefully his eyes will be
so filled with tears of joy,

38:47.000 --> 38:49.999
he won't notice the actual state
of his birthday cake.

38:49.999 --> 38:54.999
all:
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

38:54.999 --> 38:57.999
- Whoo!

38:57.999 --> 38:58.999
[all cheering]

38:58.999 --> 39:01.999
- Happy birthday.
- Wow.

39:01.999 --> 39:02.999
[laughs]

39:02.999 --> 39:04.999
- I want to turn 50
a couple more times.

39:04.999 --> 39:05.999
[laughter]

39:05.999 --> 39:08.999
- You literally got the best
50-year-old birthday party

39:08.999 --> 39:10.999
a guy could ask for.
- No doubt.

39:10.999 --> 39:12.999
- We have one last surprise
for you on the swim platform.

39:12.999 --> 39:15.999
- I was happy with this.
That's crazy.

39:15.999 --> 39:17.999
- You guys ready?

39:18.999 --> 39:21.999
[fireworks exploding]

39:21.999 --> 39:24.999
- Whoa!
- Whoo!

39:24.999 --> 39:27.999
- Come on, fireworks?
- Oh, yeah.

39:27.999 --> 39:29.999
- I love it!

39:29.999 --> 39:32.999
- This has been the worst
24 hours on a boat in my life.

39:32.999 --> 39:35.999
I'm so relieved these guests
are finally leaving.

39:35.999 --> 39:38.999
[all cheering]

39:38.999 --> 39:42.000
- You just woke up a whole
island for your birthday.

39:42.999 --> 39:44.999
- Attention all crew.

39:44.999 --> 39:46.999
I need everybody
on the aft deck in five.

39:52.999 --> 39:55.999
- I can't even look
at you right now.

39:55.999 --> 39:56.999
- Let's go. Get it out here.
- What are you talking about?

39:56.999 --> 39:58.999
This is the rest of the crew.

39:58.999 --> 39:59.999
That's all that's left of us.
- Right?

39:59.999 --> 40:01.999
[laughter]
- Works for me.

40:01.999 --> 40:03.999
I just want to put this thing
to bed.

40:05.999 --> 40:09.999
- Junior.
- Hello.

40:09.999 --> 40:12.999
- Thank you.
- So great.

40:12.999 --> 40:15.999
- Captain Lee.
- That would be awesome.

40:15.999 --> 40:17.999
It's, like, 10:30 at night.

40:17.999 --> 40:18.999
The guests seemed happy,
but honestly,

40:18.999 --> 40:20.999
I'm just too tired
to even care,

40:20.999 --> 40:23.999
and I hope they will never
approve another late departure.

40:23.999 --> 40:24.999
- I don't know what to say.
- Happy birthday.

40:24.999 --> 40:26.999
- It's a pretty
amazing birthday, yeah?

40:26.999 --> 40:28.999
- You think?
- Once in a lifetime.

40:28.999 --> 40:33.999
And from the bottom of my heart,
from my family to you guys,

40:33.999 --> 40:34.999
thank you so much.

40:34.999 --> 40:36.999
And a little something
for you and the crew--

40:36.999 --> 40:38.999
you guys earned every dollar.

40:38.999 --> 40:40.999
It was a pretty
amazing birthday.

40:40.999 --> 40:41.999
- Glad we got to share it
with you, man.

40:41.999 --> 40:42.999
- You take care.
- See you, buddy.

40:42.999 --> 40:44.999
- All right.
- Thank you.

40:44.999 --> 40:46.999
- Bye, friends.
- Bye!

40:46.999 --> 40:49.999
- Happy birthday!
- Cheers.

40:49.999 --> 40:51.999
- Love y'all.
-	 Salud.

40:51.999 --> 40:53.999
- Let's wrap it up.
Everybody turn in.

40:53.999 --> 40:55.999
We'll do the tip meeting
in the morning.

40:56.999 --> 40:58.999
Good night.

41:09.999 --> 41:11.999
- It's so nice
to see you cook, Rocky.

41:11.999 --> 41:13.999
- Thanks, Kate.
I really enjoyed it.

41:13.999 --> 41:14.999
I had a great time doing it.

41:14.999 --> 41:19.999
This is actually what I usually
do instead of, like, do stew.

41:19.999 --> 41:20.999
- Oh.

41:20.999 --> 41:22.999
Well, Rocky...
- What? What, Kate?

41:22.999 --> 41:25.999
- That wasn't the job
that is on the boat.

41:25.999 --> 41:26.999
- Correct, Kate,
and I think I did

41:27.000 --> 41:29.999
a really frickin' awesome job

41:29.999 --> 41:33.999
stepping up
and doing the stew role.

41:33.999 --> 41:35.999
- Yeah. You did, and I've always
told you that, right?

41:35.999 --> 41:38.999
I told you you did
a great job, didn't I?

41:38.999 --> 41:40.999
- [laughs]
Oh, God.

41:40.999 --> 41:42.999
- Didn't I say
you did an amazing job,

41:42.999 --> 41:44.999
you learned really quickly,
and I was so impressed?

41:44.999 --> 41:46.999
She's just like
a ticking time bomb

41:46.999 --> 41:48.999
that I have to compliment,

41:48.999 --> 41:49.999
and even when I compliment her,

41:49.999 --> 41:51.999
I still end up
getting yelled at.

41:51.999 --> 41:55.999
- Kate, you are awesome.
You are seriously awesome.

41:55.999 --> 41:57.999
You are so awesome.
You are...

41:57.999 --> 41:58.999
- I'm really confused.
- Amazing.

41:58.999 --> 42:00.999
- I feel like you're
not being authentic.

42:00.999 --> 42:01.999
I feel like I always told you--

42:01.999 --> 42:03.999
- I'm not being authentic.
You're right.

42:03.999 --> 42:06.999
Maybe I'm not being authentic
right now.

42:06.999 --> 42:09.999
Chef left today,
and I think that was baloney.

42:09.999 --> 42:11.999
You helped
make that decision, Kate.

42:11.999 --> 42:12.999
You totally helped
make that decision,

42:12.999 --> 42:14.999
and that's where my attitude
is right now.

42:14.999 --> 42:16.999
- I don't even know
why he left.

42:16.999 --> 42:18.999
- You know what you're
really good at, Kate?

42:18.999 --> 42:20.999
You're good at these sharp,
little jabs.

42:20.999 --> 42:21.999
You're a jabber.

42:21.999 --> 42:24.999
You just jab, jab,
jab, jab, jab.

42:24.999 --> 42:26.999
"Hi, my name's Kate."
Jab.

42:26.999 --> 42:27.999
- You know
what you're really good at?

42:27.999 --> 42:29.999
- What, Kate?
Tell me.

42:29.999 --> 42:31.999
- Showing no respect
for people

42:31.999 --> 42:34.999
who have earned their position
and for positions--

42:34.999 --> 42:36.999
You need to let me finish!

42:36.999 --> 42:38.999
- When you want respect,
you got to give respect.

42:38.999 --> 42:42.999
You have been so rude
to the chef, to me.

42:42.999 --> 42:44.999
- I've been very nice to you.
- Wrong. Wrong.

42:44.999 --> 42:45.999
- If you didn't think
I was nice to you,

42:45.999 --> 42:47.999
you wouldn't still be here.

42:47.999 --> 42:49.999
- And then walk
away from a conversation,

42:49.999 --> 42:50.999
'cause I'm a child.

42:50.999 --> 42:53.999
- At this point,
Rocky is useless to me.

42:53.999 --> 42:55.999
Ain't nobody got time

42:55.999 --> 42:59.999
for Rocky and her 17 different
[bleep] personalities.

42:59.999 --> 43:02.999
- I'm done.
Done, dude.

43:02.999 --> 43:04.999
- You're [bleep] awesome.
- I'm sorry, dude.

43:04.999 --> 43:06.999
I've been trying my hardest.

43:06.999 --> 43:07.999
How long can you try?
How long can I try?

43:07.999 --> 43:09.999
- Rocky, I love you, okay?

43:09.999 --> 43:12.999
[both laughing]

43:12.999 --> 43:15.999
- Coming up...

43:15.999 --> 43:18.999
- Hello, darling.
[laughs]

43:18.999 --> 43:19.999
- What are you doing here?

43:25.999 --> 43:27.999
- How's it going?
- Going good.

43:27.999 --> 43:28.999
Lots of progress.

43:28.999 --> 43:30.999
- That looks really good,
actually.

43:30.999 --> 43:32.999
- Hi, Amy Jo.
- Hi.

43:32.999 --> 43:34.999
- How are you?

43:34.999 --> 43:35.999
- Good. How are you?
- Good.

43:35.999 --> 43:37.999
- I don't know
what to say to Rocky,

43:37.999 --> 43:39.999
because I feel like she owes us
all some sort of apology,

43:39.999 --> 43:42.999
but I don't think she realizes
she did anything wrong.

43:43.000 --> 43:46.999
- I'm having a hard time getting
in a good space with Rocky.

43:46.999 --> 43:48.999
Like, how do you go
from jumping off the boat

43:48.999 --> 43:52.999
and swimming away,
coming back like, "I'm here"?

43:53.999 --> 43:54.999
Yeah.

43:54.999 --> 43:56.999
- If Rocky's in a bad mood,

43:56.999 --> 43:58.999
it's like, "Guys, I'm not
in the mood right now."

43:58.999 --> 44:00.999
And then two seconds later,
she's like, "Hey!"

44:00.999 --> 44:02.000
- She is eternally

44:02.999 --> 44:04.999
on an emotional roller coaster
all the time,

44:04.999 --> 44:06.999
and she expects us all to go
on the ride with her.

44:06.999 --> 44:07.999
I don't care
if she apologizes.

44:07.999 --> 44:09.999
I just want off the crazy ride

44:09.999 --> 44:10.999
so that Amy and I can do
the real work.

44:10.999 --> 44:13.000
- Words are easy.
- Yeah, talk is cheap.

44:13.999 --> 44:15.999
And also, you were
a [bleep] bitch in the galley.

44:15.999 --> 44:18.999
And your [bleep] plating sucks.

44:19.000 --> 44:21.000
I'm already embarrassed
about what I did,

44:21.000 --> 44:22.999
and it's hypocritical of me.

44:22.999 --> 44:24.999
It's morally
and ethically wrong.

44:24.999 --> 44:26.999
It goes against everything
that I stand for,

44:26.999 --> 44:29.999
but then to have
her really go off the deep end

44:29.999 --> 44:31.000
on the psychotic range...

44:31.000 --> 44:32.999
And I just want
to distance myself from her

44:32.999 --> 44:34.999
as much as I possibly can.

44:34.999 --> 44:36.999
- I think we're all
just kind of, like, baffled that

44:36.999 --> 44:38.999
that happened and that there's--
- No repercussions.

44:38.999 --> 44:40.999
- Nothing,
or she's not even, like,

44:40.999 --> 44:42.999
really sympathetic
about it.

44:42.999 --> 44:43.999
I guess I'm just going
to keep on focusing on work

44:44.000 --> 44:45.999
and get through
these next two charters.

44:45.999 --> 44:47.999
- Yep, it's all we can do.

44:47.999 --> 44:48.999
- Attention all crew.

44:48.999 --> 44:52.000
I need everybody
in the crew mess in two.

44:55.999 --> 44:56.999
- You got to stay with us
eight more days.

44:56.999 --> 44:59.999
Eight more days.
Can't lose it yet.

44:59.999 --> 45:02.999
- Fires,
stew abandoning ship,

45:02.999 --> 45:05.999
Chef walking off mid-charter,
grenadine oysters--

45:05.999 --> 45:08.999
this charter has been
an absolute disaster.

45:10.999 --> 45:11.999
- What a [bleep]show, huh?
- [chuckles]

45:11.999 --> 45:15.999
- Now you know why [bleep] lions
eat their young.

45:15.999 --> 45:18.999
I think the worst one
I ever worked on,

45:18.999 --> 45:20.999
but these guys were happy.

45:20.999 --> 45:24.000
All right,
$17,500 split 9 ways--

45:24.999 --> 45:27.999
$1,950 for each one of us.

45:27.999 --> 45:30.999
Rocky. Emile.

45:30.999 --> 45:32.999
- Rocky should have gotten down
on her hands and [bleep] knees

45:32.999 --> 45:34.999
and apologized
to that entire crew

45:34.999 --> 45:35.999
during the tip meeting.

45:35.999 --> 45:37.999
- Got everybody, didn't I?

45:37.999 --> 45:39.999
I have a bit of a surprise
for you guys this morning.

45:39.999 --> 45:41.999
We're getting a new chef.

45:41.999 --> 45:44.999
We will get through
the next two charters.

45:44.999 --> 45:47.999
We got two left.
Don't let up, please.

45:47.999 --> 45:49.999
We need to get busy.

45:49.999 --> 45:51.999
Let's flip the boat.
- Thanks, Cap.

45:56.999 --> 45:58.999
- I thought last night
was really lovely.

45:58.999 --> 46:00.999
Chef would have been proud.

46:00.999 --> 46:02.999
- Yeah.
You ask if you could be chef?

46:02.999 --> 46:04.999
- That wasn't even an option.

46:04.999 --> 46:06.999
I'm surprised, though.

46:06.999 --> 46:08.999
At the same time,
I don't want to be...

46:08.999 --> 46:09.999
- Oh, whatever.

46:09.999 --> 46:10.999
- No, I don't want
to be chef with her.

46:10.999 --> 46:12.999
- Oh.
Oh, okay.

46:12.999 --> 46:14.999
- To be completely honest,
I'm just excited

46:14.999 --> 46:15.999
to have some new blood.

46:15.999 --> 46:17.999
They don't know me.

46:17.999 --> 46:19.999
I don't know them.
They don't know anybody.

46:19.999 --> 46:21.999
Like, no more negative stuff,
no more negative stuff.

46:21.999 --> 46:23.999
Let's think positive.
[exhales deeply]

46:24.000 --> 46:25.999
'Cause it can just make
you go crazy, you know?

46:28.999 --> 46:31.999
[funky rock music]

46:31.999 --> 46:36.999
♪ ♪

46:36.999 --> 46:37.999
- Hello, darling.

46:37.999 --> 46:40.999
[both laugh]

46:40.999 --> 46:42.999
- What are you doing here?

46:42.999 --> 46:44.999
- How's it going?
- Ah!

46:44.999 --> 46:45.999
Oh, my gosh.

46:45.999 --> 46:46.999
- Hello, lovelies.

46:46.999 --> 46:49.999
I am Ben Robinson,
and I'm a yacht chef.

46:49.999 --> 46:50.999
[laughs]

46:51.000 --> 46:53.999
- This is Ben, our new chef.
both: Nice to meet you.

46:53.999 --> 46:55.999
Looking a little pretty.
- He does look pretty right now.

46:55.999 --> 46:57.999
He's so delicate.

46:57.999 --> 47:00.999
- Unfortunately, I wasn't
available for Captain Lee

47:00.999 --> 47:02.999
to start this season with him,

47:02.999 --> 47:05.999
but I'm really,
really just happy to be here.

47:05.999 --> 47:06.999
- Hey.
- Good to see you.

47:06.999 --> 47:07.999
Thanks for the call.
- Oh.

47:07.999 --> 47:11.000
- Yeah, I just thought I'd make
an effort for you, you know.

47:11.000 --> 47:13.999
- Ben looks good.
He's great with the crew.

47:13.999 --> 47:16.999
Great sense of humor.
It's 180 degrees from Leon.

47:16.999 --> 47:18.999
- Do you mind if I ask
what happened with the chef?

47:18.999 --> 47:20.999
'Cause it might help me.

47:20.999 --> 47:22.999
- Um...
stubborn as hell.

47:22.999 --> 47:24.999
- Mm-hmm.
- Not that you're--

47:24.999 --> 47:27.999
- No, I just hide it better.

47:27.999 --> 47:29.999
It's actually quite common

47:29.999 --> 47:32.999
for a chef not to work out
during a charter season.

47:32.999 --> 47:36.999
So I've actually been the guy
several times to rescue boats.

47:36.999 --> 47:37.999
- But I think the biggest
problem down in the galley

47:37.999 --> 47:39.999
is communicating
with the chief stew.

47:39.999 --> 47:40.999
- It was like a funeral home
in there.

47:40.999 --> 47:42.000
Nobody would speak.

47:42.999 --> 47:44.999
- She needs, like,
a little release.

47:44.999 --> 47:45.999
- [laughs]

47:45.999 --> 47:47.999
- Just the man, huh?
[laughs]

47:47.999 --> 47:50.999
- One way to put it.
- That one.

47:50.999 --> 47:53.999
Kate and I didn't always
get on last season.

47:53.999 --> 47:56.999
- I'm kind of tired
of listening to you talk.

47:56.999 --> 47:57.999
- All right.
You're [bleep] at what you do.

47:57.999 --> 47:59.999
She's [bleep] wrong.

47:59.999 --> 48:00.999
- [sniffles]

48:01.000 --> 48:04.999
- But since then, we've managed
to patch things up,

48:04.999 --> 48:09.000
and we've had a couple of
romantic flings here and there.

48:09.999 --> 48:11.999
You know, it's just sex,
though, isn't it?

48:11.999 --> 48:13.999
[laughs]

48:13.999 --> 48:16.999
Hello, love.
- Well, it took you long enough.

48:16.999 --> 48:17.999
- I know.
It's a long swim.

48:17.999 --> 48:20.999
- Oh, my God. I am so relieved
to see Ben on the boat.

48:20.999 --> 48:22.999
Finally, there's going to be
some laughter in the galley.

48:22.999 --> 48:24.999
- How's it all going?
- Better now.

48:24.999 --> 48:26.999
- Good.
- Yeah.

48:26.999 --> 48:29.999
- Let's check this little
monster out, shall we?

48:29.999 --> 48:32.999
- I have no idea where Ben
and I are relationship-wise.

48:32.999 --> 48:34.999
I mean, I love Ben.
We're best friends.

48:34.999 --> 48:36.999
I love being around him,
'cause we laugh,

48:36.999 --> 48:38.999
but I don't think we should date
because we're too alike.

48:38.999 --> 48:40.999
- This is the new chef.

48:40.999 --> 48:42.999
- No way.
Hi. I'm so excited.

48:42.999 --> 48:45.999
We have a good chef to look by
when we walk through the galley.

48:45.999 --> 48:47.999
- You're making me very bashful
right now, love.

48:47.999 --> 48:52.999
[both laugh]

48:52.999 --> 48:53.999
- Well...

48:53.999 --> 48:57.999
I've heard quite a bit
about Ben from Kate--

48:57.999 --> 48:58.999
that he's a lot of fun.

48:58.999 --> 48:59.999
- Take you downstairs.

48:59.999 --> 49:01.999
- And he's really good
in bed.

49:01.999 --> 49:03.999
[giggles]

49:03.999 --> 49:06.999
- Oh, my--
- Hello, love. How are you?

49:06.999 --> 49:07.999
- Hi! Good!

49:07.999 --> 49:09.999
- Hello.
It's good to see you.

49:09.999 --> 49:11.999
- Have you come to save us?

49:11.999 --> 49:12.999
- I don't know
what I'm here for.

49:12.999 --> 49:14.999
- He is. He's our salvation.
- Oh, my gosh.

49:14.999 --> 49:16.999
- I'm either going to save you
or ruin you.

49:16.999 --> 49:18.999
[Eddie laughs]

49:18.999 --> 49:21.999
- Ben brings a whole different
vibe and energy to the boat.

49:21.999 --> 49:23.999
